<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/208.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Alger</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mazatlan</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 11. Have no communication outside city. Understand all mining
                            companies in Sinaloa called on to pay and are paying or have paid. W.
                            Felton, E. H. Hoag and Chas. Thomas, residents Mazatlan, inform they
                            have paid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alger</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>